With the lines we appended to the config file we configured AIDE to check the folder /etc for changes, so let's make a file change and check for it with AIDE. We'll start by checking for changes, and we'll see there are none - we've only just created the database. Then we'll make an inconsequential edit to the file /etc/pam.conf and then use AIDE to check for changes
....................................................................................................................
kali@kali:~$ sudo aide -c /etc/aide/aide.conf
kali@kali:~$ echo -e "# New Comment\n$(cat /etc/pam.conf)" >> /etc/pam.conf
kali@kali:~$ sudo aide -c /etc/aide/aide.conf
